        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 8 at 6:49AM EDT by NWS Peachtree City GA</headline>
        <description>At 649 AM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was over Stovall, or 10 miles
southeast of LaGrange, moving east at 45 mph.

HAZARD...Winds 40 to 50 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
LaGrange, Greenville, Manchester, West Point, Pine Mountain, Warm
Springs, Shiloh, Raleigh, Mountville, Cannonville, Odessadale, State
Line Park, Stovall, Piedmont Heights, Big Springs, Durand, Baughs
Crossroads, Harris City, Smiths Crossroad, and Long Cane.
</description>
        <instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately.</instruction>
